No personal experience, as I don't like to tickle the dragon, but I think that the torque warning is in enough places as to be taken 
seriously.

I've been using Hylomar non-hardening sealer on drain plugs, gaskets, and similar sealing surfaces and it seems to really help oil weeping 
problems,  It's now sold by Permatex for about $4 a tube.

